import React from 'react'
import {BrowserRouter, Routes, Route} from 'react-router-dom'
import { AuthContextProvider } from './contexts/AuthContext'
import Signup from './pages/Signup'
import Login from './pages/Login'
import Navbar from './components/Navbar'
import Home from './components/Home'
import Card from './components/Card'
import './App.css'
const App = () => {
  const blogs=[{
    title: "My first blog",
    content: "Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur, adipisicing elit. Molestiae temporibus, fuga explicabo consectetur tempora earum dolor id atque voluptatibus optio quas ipsa eius eaque aliquam, esse, placeat molestias officiis alias maiores! Voluptatibus, quas cumque id fugiat neque autem magni consequatur doloremque quia voluptas quidem dolorum eius facere, eligendi eum. Voluptatum, maxime. Earum autem doloribus quis deserunt. Impedit iure voluptatum sunt, odit rem dignissimos minima, voluptatibus nihil obcaecati cumque quisquam, sapiente ipsam magni neque! Obcaecati recusandae minima, minus sit dicta reprehenderit nemo atque facere fugiat cupiditate inventore nam eaque omnis, harum voluptates distinctio rerum placeat. Non eaque ducimus cupiditate et ipsa.",
    author: "Peach Agarwal",
    postedOn: new Date()
  }]
  return (
    <>
      {/* <AuthContextProvider>
        <BrowserRouter>
          <Navbar/>
          <Routes>
            <Route path="/" element={<Home/>} />
            <Route path="/signup" element={<Signup/>} />
            <Route path="/login" element={<Login/>} />
          </Routes>
        </BrowserRouter>
      </AuthContextProvider> */}
      {/* {console.log("title", blogs[0].title)} */}
      <Card title={blogs[0].title} content={blogs[0].content} author={blogs[0].author} postedOn={blogs[0].postedOn}/>
    </>
  )
}

export default App
